      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mix, knead, and bulk ferment, 1 hour",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Combine {{strong-bread-flour}}, {{yeast-fast-action}}, {{salt-table}}, and {{caster-sugar}}. Add the {{whole-milk}}, {{eggs}}, and {{unsalted-butter}} from the dough group. Mix to a soft, slightly sticky dough. Knead for 10 minutes until smooth and elastic, enriched doughs take longer to come together than plain ones. Cover and leave until doubled, about 1 hour.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Fill, roll, and prove, 30 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mix the filling {{light-brown-sugar}} and {{cinnamon-ground}} together. Roll the dough into a rectangle roughly 30 × 45 cm. Spread the filling {{unsalted-butter}} over the surface, then scatter the cinnamon sugar mix, pressing lightly so it sticks. Roll tightly from the long edge into an even cylinder. Cut into 9 equal rounds. Line a rectangular tin (roughly 23 × 30 cm) with baking paper and arrange the rolls cut-side up with a little space between them. Cover and prove for 30 minutes until touching and visibly risen. Heat the oven to 180°C (160°C fan).",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake and frost",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake for 22 to 25 minutes until pale gold on top, these rolls colour less than a standard bread. While they cool, beat {{cream-cheese}} with the frosting {{unsalted-butter}}, {{icing-sugar}}, and {{vanilla-extract}} until smooth. Spread thickly over the rolls after 10 minutes out of the oven.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
